From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 7 Feb 2026 18:16:18 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] clk: Add ACPI clock infrastructure for CIX Sky1

Add two components for ACPI clock support on CIX Sky1 SoCs:

1. clk-scmi: Under ACPI, register each SCMI clock via clkdev for
   global lookup instead of using the DT-only of_clk_add_hw_provider.
   ACPI firmware does not enumerate every CPU, interconnect, PCIe, DDR,
   and boot-critical clock consumer, so mark these clocks CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED
   in the ACPI path to avoid disabling firmware-owned boot resources during
   the generic unused-clock sweep.

2. clk-sky1-acpi (CIXHA010): New driver that walks the ACPI namespace
   to parse CLKT tables on each device node, creating clkdev entries
   that connect SCMI-provided clocks to their consumer devices. This
   is the ACPI equivalent of DT phandle-based clock references.
---
